21/63 US national parks done ✅ .  My way of celebrating holidays in nature. SAGUARO 🌵 NATIONAL PARK. 🏞️.

Had to wait for 10 hours for the sky to clear up to get this picture. The wait was well worth it. From overcast in the morning to clear skies in the afternoon.

“Where cacti touch the sky and dreams take flight… 🌅🌵 #DesertDreaming”, living my dream life . My Christmas tree this year. Happy Christmas 🎄 #####happiness overloaded.

The giant saguaro is the universal symbol of the American west. These majestic plants, found only in a small portion of the United States, are protected by Saguaro National Park, to the east and west of the modern city of Tucson. 

The saguaro features a pleated surface which allows it to expand to contain all the water it needs: it can hold over a thousand gallons. During dry times, it can pull from this source to grow and produce flowers and seeds. When fully loaded, the cactus won’t need to absorb water for an entire year.

“Life’s most beautiful moments bloom in the desert… 🌺🌵 #DesertBlooms” “Desert vibes and cacti dreams… 🌵🌟 #DesertLife”

22/63 ✅ CARSLSBAD CAVERNS NATIONAL PARK 

Carlsbad Caverns National Park is designated a World Heritage Site. Within Carlsbad Cavern, The Big Room is 8.2 acres (3.3 hectares)— the largest, readily accessible cave chamber in North America.

The Natural Entrance Trail is a steep 1-1/4 mile (2 km) descent, equivalent to about 79 stories, from the Natural Entrance to the Big Room. The entire 79 stories hike takes around 4.5 to complete the entire loop. The big room is accessible. To be honest the pictures clicked on I phone is not able to justify the beauty of this massive limestone cave. 

It’s a must visit place in New Mexico.
